Former eThekekwini mayor Zandile Gumede is facing corruption charges related to the awarding of a dodgy multi-million rand Durban Solid Waste tender. JOHANNESBURG - Former eThekwini Mayor Zandile Gumede will appear at the Durban Commercial Crimes Court on Wednesday. She is facing corruption charges related to the awarding of a dodgy multi-million rand Durban Solid Waste tender. WATCH: New eThekwini mayor elected In October last year, more than R50-million in assets were seized from alleged fraudsters, including Gumede. The Asset Forfeiture Unit (AFU) and the Hawks cracked down on 16 people linked to the multi-million fraud case. Courtesy #DStv403 The Asset Forfeiture Unit (AFU) and the Hawks cracked down on 16 people linked to the multi-million fraud case. WATCH: I am as poor as a church mouse, says Zandile Gumede Other municipal officials and contractors have also been charged. Gumede was forced to resign following these fraud and corruption charges.